cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of learning object structures in an image modeling process without supervision. It proposes an autoencoding formulation to discover landmarks as explicit structural representations. The paper uses deep neural networks and proposes an end-to-end differentiable framework. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses constraints to ensure the validity of landmarks, which is a topic in the sub-category cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Finally, the paper uses deep neural networks, which is a topic in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
